claims:
Claims WHAT IS CLAIMED IS: A system, comprising: a touchscreen; and a controller coupled to the touchscreen, the controller configured to: adjust performance of the touchscreen through dynamically setting a controller parameter to support altered touch reporting in at least one first area of the touchscreen relative to a second area of the touchscreen; and control enablement of touch detection for the at least one first area according to performance characteristics associated with an application operating in the second area. The system of claim 1, wherein the touchscreen comprises a plurality of driven lines, and the controller is further configured to: activate at least one driven line of the plurality of driven lines at a time; and determine, in real time, the at least one driven line to activate. The system of claim 2, wherein the controller parameter comprises: a subset of driven lines of the plurality of driven lines associated with the at least one first area, wherein the at least one first area is smaller than the second area. The system of claim 3, wherein the controller is further configured to receive at least one altered touch reporting parameter, and wherein the at least one altered touch reporting parameter comprises at least one of: dimensions of the at least one first area, dimensions of a no-scan area, a scan rate of the at least one first area, and enrichment data. The system of claim 4, wherein the at least one first area is static on the touchscreen. The system of claim 4, wherein the at least one first area is a fast scan area. The system of claim 6, wherein the at least one first area is dynamic on the touchscreen, and moves according to a detected touch location. 8. The system of claim 6, wherein to further control enablement, the controller is further configured to: identify a user associated with the at least one first area. 9. The system of claim 8, wherein to identify the user, the controller is further configured to: receive a watermarked touch signal from the at least one first area, wherein the watermarked touch signal comprises a touch signal and a unique signal; analyze the watermarked touch signal; detect a touch location; and detect the unique signal, wherein the unique signal is associated with the user. 10. The system of claim 9, wherein the unique signal is associated with a drive frequency of the controller. 11. The system of claim 10, wherein the unique signal includes a unique code modulated to the drive frequency, and wherein the unique signal is a low voltage signal. 12. The system of claim 11, wherein the unique code is an orthogonal code. 13. The system of claim 9, wherein the unique signal is associated with one drive frequency of the controller, wherein a second unique signal is associated with a different drive frequency of the of the controller. 14. The system of claim 13, wherein each associated drive frequency is paired with a code, and a combination of each associated drive frequency and code is unique. 15. The system of claim 8, further comprising: a touch pad coupled to the touchscreen, wherein the touch pad is configured to: capture an identifying image of a hand of the user; and transfers the unique signal to the user when the user touches the touch pad, wherein the at least one first area is positioned in proximity with the touch pad. 16. The system of claim 15, wherein when the user touches the second area, the controller is further configured to: 

 receive a second watermarked touch signal from the second area, wherein the second watermarked touch signal comprises a second touch signal and the unique signal; and analyze the second watermarked touch signal to detect the unique signal. 17. The system of claim 4, wherein the at least one first area is a slow scan area. 18. The system of claim 17, further comprising: a sensor in contact with the at least one first area, wherein the sensor is configured to: detect changes in at least one of: temperature, pressure, and weight; and adjust an electric field of the sensor accordingly; and the controller further configured to: detect the electric field adjustment. 19. The system of claim 18, wherein the sensor comprises: a metal strip comprising at least two metals with different coefficients of expansion, wherein a shape of the metal strip alters according to a change in temperature. 20. The system of claim 18, wherein the sensor comprises: a spring whose height changes with a change in pressure or mass. 21. The system of claim 8, wherein to identify the user, the controller is further configured to: receive touch signal from the at least one first area; detect a touch location; and detect a palm print, wherein the palm print is associated with the user. 22. The system of claim 8, wherein the controller is further configured to: maintain user identification through signal communication to and from a device in contact with the user. 23. The system of claim 22, wherein the controller is further configured to: detect a user touch in the at least one first area; 

 receive a signal from the device, wherein the signal comprises: a unique serial number identifying the user, and a detected driver signal corresponding to the user touch; and correlate the user touch detected with the user. 24. A method, comprising: adjusting performance of a touchscreen through dynamically setting a controller parameter to support a altered touch reporting in at least one first area of the touchscreen relative to a second area of the touchscreen; and controlling enablement of touch detection for the at least one first area according to performance characteristics associated with an application operating in the second area. 25. A non-transitory computer readable medium carrying one or more sequences of one or more instructions for execution by one or more processors to perform operations, comprising: adjusting performance of a touchscreen through dynamically setting a controller parameter to support altered touch reporting in at least one first area of the touchscreen relative to a second area of the touchscreen; and controlling enablement of touch detection for the at least one first area according to performance characteristics associated with an application operating in the second area.
